* value that perhaps do not exist should be represented by an "optional type", which is usually named "Option" or rather "Maybe"; this is better solution than the null value
	* link to explanation
		\ links-to internal fbctgaodsnjovfll
* exceptional return values should be returned by wrapping the return value of the function into an "Either" type that is an algebraic data type that has 2 states : either the normal value or the exceptional one; this is better solution than throwing and catching exceptions
	* link to explanation
		\ links-to internal jiwpglhclkfxvqoh
